        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         This fix really rocks.  However, the DC change, or lack of change, isnt a good one, at all.  Yes my DC pet hits about twice as hard, but the fact is, in basically all situations a summoned pet is going to be better.  Because it's all about exp, and I'd rather have a pet that hits for 65 and takes no exp than a pet that hits for 125 and takes proportional exp.</P><P>I think the fact that DC takes 9 AA's, is buggy, pets suicide, players go LD, has a 2 hour recast time, etc, should make it balanced for a player with direcharm to get the same bonus as summoned pets.</P><P>It just sucks that if i went out to the grey now for some exp, I'd DEFINATLY use a spectre or a rogue over direcharm.  And that's really what matters the most.  The timesinks and risks associated with direcharm make it deserve the same fix as summoned pets.</P><P>Yes, this will allow DC chanters to solo very well, but without auto-DW and a way to heal their pets it's not all that overpowering.  And it wont be faster than an uber monk with a pocket druid.</P><P><img src="http://www.mnickey.com/zon_sig.gif" border=0><BR>-Zondro Devilldoll 60 GWARLOCK of Karana<BR>(VERY BAD)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21774" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21774</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
